Making it without looking 👀 to show you how easy it is 👌🏽 PARĀOA PARAI (FRY BREAD) Makes: 20 1 cup chilled miraka (milk) ¾ cup boiling wai (water) 1 Tbspn īhi (yeast) 1 Tbspn huka (sugar) 4 Tbspn hinu (oil) 4-4.5 cups puehu parāoa (flour) 1.5 tsp tote (salt) + oil for frying Mix all ingredients except flour and salt in a large bowl. Leave for 15 mins. Add flour and salt (start with 4 cups, and add more if it’s too sticky), gently combine, knead for a few minutes, then rest 1 hr, or until doubled in size. Lightly oil the bench, then press out dough and divide into squares by rolling a plate along it. Fry in hot oil till puffed + golden. Transfer to a dish lined with paper towels. Devour 🔥🤤 My one rule if you make this: make extra (I usually double the recipe) to bless a neighbour, kaumātua or someone living alone 🖤 For the full method, tips, and chef’s notes, visit our website: www.maimoa.nz/frybread #frybread #friedbread
